        }
      ],
      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">In individuals experiencing hemolysis, the long-term control of blood sugar levels cannot be accurately assessed using glycated hemoglobin (HbA1c) due to the shortened lifespan of red blood cells. Instead, another biomarker must be utilized. Fructosamine, which refers to glycated serum proteins such as albumin, has been suggested as an alternative measure. Is the statement that fructosamine is a glycated albumin true or false?&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q7194902",
      "question_audio": null,
      "question_video": null,
      "map_id": 29851,
      "difficulty_level": "intermediate",
      "subjects_id": [
        1
      ],
      "solution": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Ans. A) True.</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Option A:</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Along with other proteins, albumin is also glycated in diabetes mellitus.</span></span></span></li>\r\n\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Glycated albumin is called fructosamine albumin.</span></span></span></li>\r\n\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">As half-life of albumin is 20 days, gluco-albumin concentration reflects the glucose control over the last 2-3 weeks. </span></span></span></li>\r\n\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Estimation of serum fructosamine is preferred in gestational diabetes mellitus.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Educational Objective: </span></u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"><strong>Fructosamine</strong> is a <strong>measure of glycemic control</strong> that can be <strong>used as an alternative to HbA1c, </strong>particularly in situations where <strong>red blood cell turnover is increased</strong>, such as <strong>hemolysis</strong>. It specifically <strong>reflects the glycation of serum proteins</strong> like <strong>albumin </strong>over a shorter time frame.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Ref:</span></u></strong><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"> Vasudevan 9/e p 330. </span></strong></span></span></p>",
